f=Brand Studio/nate/marketplace/ab-test-analysis/SKILL.md · tx=<!-- Unmodified copy "ab-test-analysis" (phuryn/pm-skills, 22k★ repo already trusted marcus's sources), fulfilling catalog's ab-testing-stats slot ("sample size, significance, peeking discipline: pre-register metric MDE; peeking before report p"). skill carries three plus SRM checks, novelty-effect washout, guardrail-metric discipline, ship/extend/stop/investigate decision table. NOTES SYSTEM: statistical law experiment-backlog's pre-registration phase enforces two run one discipline. generates runs Python calculations raw data provided one Python needs Brand Studio; noted nate's tool requirements. Rule 0.6 note: rare skill formula-grounded (z-tests, power analysis) outputs statistics, rubrics; rubric flag applies ICE upstream, here. --> · h2:A/B Test Analysis=Evaluate A/B test results statistical rigor translate findings clear product decisions. · h3:Context=You analyzing A/B test results **$ARGUMENTS**. user provides data files (CSV, Excel, analytics exports), read analyze them directly. Generate Python scripts statistical calculations needed. · h3:Instructions=1. **Understand the experiment**: · h3:Instructions=What was the hypothesis?, What changed (the variant)?, What primary metric? Any guardrail metrics?, long test run?, What traffic split? · h3:Instructions=**Validate test setup**: · h3:Instructions=**Sample size**: sample large enough expected effect size?, Use formula: (Z²α/2 (1-p)) MDE², Flag test underpowered (<80% power), **Duration**: test run least 1-2 full business cycles?, **Randomization**: Any evidence sample ratio mismatch (SRM)?, **Novelty/primacy effects**: enough time wash out initial behavior changes? · h3:Instructions=3. **Calculate statistical significance**: · h3:Instructions=**Conversion rate** control variant, **Relative lift**: (variant control) control 100, **p-value**: Using two-tailed z-test chi-squared test, **Confidence interval**: 95% difference, **Statistical significance**: 0.05?, **Practical significance**: lift meaningful business? · h3:Instructions=user provides raw data, generate run Python script calculate these. **Check guardrail metrics**: · h3:Instructions=any guardrail metrics (revenue, engagement, page load time) degrade?, winning primary metric degraded guardrails true win · h3:Instructions=5. **Interpret results**: · h3:Instructions=\| Outcome \| Recommendation \| · h3:Instructions=\|---\|---\| · h3:Instructions=\| Significant positive lift, no guardrail issues \| **Ship it** — roll out to 100% \| · h3:Instructions=\| Significant positive lift, guardrail concerns \| **Investigate** — understand trade-offs before shipping \| · h3:Instructions=\| Not significant, positive trend \| **Extend the test** — need more data or larger effect \| · h3:Instructions=\| Not significant, flat \| **Stop the test** — no meaningful difference detected \| · h3:Instructions=\| Significant negative lift \| **Don't ship** — revert to control, analyze why \| · h3:Instructions=`## A/B Test Results: [Test Name] \·  \· **Hypothesis**: [What we expected] \· **Duration**: [X days] \| **Sample**: [N control / M variant] \· ` · h3:Instructions=**Provide analysis summary**: Think step step. Save markdown. Generate Python scripts calculations raw data provided.